import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='X', y='Y', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='X', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['X'].mean(), color='red', label=f'mean: {data["X"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
